title: David Duchovny
itunes:title: David Duchovny
description:
David Duchovny [The X-Files, Californication, Aquarius, The Bubble] talks with Anna (from inside a railroad car) about the movie they recently finished together, being intimidated by raw talent, his love of music, the challenges of writing, dealbreakers, what defines a good kiss, words to live by and much more.


Today’s first call is with Savannah whose recent relationships have affected her self-esteem, causing her to rethink her dating strategy.


Next, Anna and David talk with Melissa, whose wedding plans have upset a close friend, leading to Melissa’s own unhappiness.


Hosted on Acast. See acast.com/privacy for more information.
